---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const config = {
    title: "Ryan Bucinell - Previous site designs",
    breadcrumbs: [
        {fa:'home', text:'Home', url: 'index.html'},
        {fa:'clock', text:'Retro Pages', url:'#'}
    ],
    page: {
        title: 'Site Revisions',
        small: 'iterations over the years'
    }
};
---
<BaseLayout config={config}>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <p>Below are pictures from my old sites. The more recent and my very first site. I find it fun to look back on what I have done in the past, and to see how much I have improved since then.</p>
            <p>After a while I get bored of my site and I can take my new ideas along with the opinions of others to upgrade it. Each time I can practice more new CSS and Javascript tricks.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="overhaul2" class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <h3 class="underline"><u>v.2</u></h3>
            <p>Implemented some color and themes. This was mostly a focus on standards and working on CSS skills</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v3_index.png" alt="retro v3 index"/></div>
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v3_code.png" alt="retro v3 code"/></div>
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v3_websites.png" alt="retro v3 websites"/></div>
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v3_resume.png" alt="retro v3 resume"/></div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" id="overhaul1">
        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <h3 class="underline"><u>v.1</u></h3>
          <p>This site was coded up with Notepad++, by my own hand, a much needed overhaul from my original site for two reasons. First, my original site was not a representation of my skill in html/css/javascript and second, I needed to make something that looked better with more space for content.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v2_index.jpg" alt="revamped Main Page"/></div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v2_graphics.jpg" alt="revamped Graphics Page"/></div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v2_resume.jpg" alt="Rich Format Resume"/></div>
      </div>
      <div class="row" id="original">
        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <h3 class="underline"><u>v.0</u></h3>
          <p>This site is hardly by skill, much of the work was done thanks to Dreamweaver, and some to my roomate Mike (thanks, man).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v1_index.jpg" alt="original main page"/></div>
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v1_projects.jpg" alt="original projects page"/></div>
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v1_about.jpg" alt="original about me page"/></div>
        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12"><img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/retro/v1_resume.jpg" alt="original resume page"/></div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>